      "side": 1,
      "message": "This decoding is problematic because the lookup table between `RefUpdate.Result` and `ReceiveCommand.Result` isn\u0027t invertible.\n\nSee https://github.com/eclipse-jgit/jgit/blob/master/org.eclipse.jgit/src/org/eclipse/jgit/transport/ReceiveCommand.java#L807.\n\nSome examples:\n\n- `ReceiveCommand.Result \u003d LOCK_FAILURE` could have been caused by `RefUpdate.Result \u003d LOCK_FAILURE` or `RefUpdate.Result \u003d IO_FAILURE`.\n\n- `ReceiveCommand.Result \u003d OK` doesn\u0027t remember which type of update was successful. It could have been `RefUpdate.Result \u003d NO_CHANGE` or `RefUpdate.Result \u003d NEW` or `RefUpdate.Result \u003d FORCED` or `RefUpdate.Result \u003d FAST_FORWARD`\n\n... and what about the `ReceiveCommand.Result \u003d REJECTED_NODELETE`, `ReceiveCommand.Result \u003d REJECT_NOCREATE`?\n\nThis status remapping is only used in the `FetchRefReplicatedEvent`, why not simply change the event and use the `ReceiveCommand.Result` instead? We may also need to store the `ReceiveCommand.Type`.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 186,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 186,
        "endChar": 79
      },
      "revId": "7c70c66542cf3ac03f84ac45d35a741ced559d91",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
